Class ServiceBrokerInvalidParametersException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • org.springframework.cloud.servicebroker.exception.ServiceBrokerException
            • org.springframework.cloud.servicebroker.exception.ServiceBrokerInvalidParametersException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class ServiceBrokerInvalidParametersException
extends ServiceBrokerException
    Thrown to indicate that parameters passed in a create or update request are not understood by the service broker.

    Throwing this exception will result in an HTTP status code 422 UNPROCESSABLE ENTITY being returned to the platform.

    Author:
    Scott Frederick
